rComments: Very nice prof. Gives a lot of textbook readings. Lessons are just powerpoints with audio, asynchronous. We had 2 forums, mid-term, and final. The forums are a great way to boost your grade, easy A!!! However, the exams are wayyy too detailed. Overall a decent class.
basically didn't have any classes, we only had videos to watch and the textbook to read and had to remember every detail of them for the multiple choice exam.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Participation matters', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: the prof seems sweet but he's totally useless. you need to buy the book because all you're gonna do is read from it. You also need to remember everything from it cuz the exam is hard, he wants us the remember the most useless infos. the group project is a waste of time. would not recommend this class

He sounds like a sweet guy, but he's honestly a really bad prof. You teach yourself the course by reading through the entire book and his powerpoints are useless. Exams are twisted ; I'm a straight A student and this class had me struggling. The group project was pointless and the TA was a tough grader. Trust me, dont take this class & save ur GPA

Online format isnt the best, all the classes are just power points with audio. Exams are majorly based on the textbook. Pretty much, you teaching yourself which isnt the best thing. Also exams were on the weekend.
He is the worst prof to take for online classes. Avoid at all cost. He isnt accessible outside of class and doesnt answer questions. He is pretty useless, you have to learn everything by yourself.

Taking this course with this prof online was pretty awful. He posted PP slides with screenshots from the textbook and short captions, he did not teach this course to me, I taught it to myself. Had to do a group project as well which i found unorganized by the TA . the only good thing was he adjusted final marks by a lot if the class didn't do well

Didn't actually teach anything this entire semester? Just gave us powerpoint slides with a sentence or so in the notes. We had these essay forums to write that everyone lost marks on because his specifications on the length of the essays could be interpreted different ways. He seems really sweet but not a good prof.

He cares about the wrong things. He copy/pastes text and asks us to watch YouTube videos while giving atrocious feedback on assignments. We have no idea how to improve because there's no continuation. He seems like a good guy but you shouldn't take him as a prof.
He does not teach at all. He literally just copy paste the textbook in the powerpoint slides.

Clearly cares about what he's doing. Terrible teacher. Lectures are slow paced and dry, tests were open book but were worded in such a way that several options could be correct depending on your reasoning. Everyone did terribly on them. Dropped the class so I can take it with a better prof.

Professor Gottret is a kind person but a terrible prof. There is no point attending his lectures as he reads directly off the slides and speaks so quietly that even with a mic he cannot be heard. For this class all testing is online, the questions have absolutely nothing to do with the lectures and you are not given enough time AT ALL to answer

Professor Gottret is an approachable professor who seems interested in his students' success. He is very soft spoken, which can make it challenging to hear his lectures at times. Having the textbook is helpful, and a close read will be helpful for exam questions.

We are tested on information that I cannot recall covering in class at all, and even if we did cover it, his test questions are so confusing that you will still struggle. There is absolutely no structure to the way he teaches.
The textbook is all you need, midterms and exams are open book. He is really soft-spoken but once you get past that he's trying his best and is a great prof.
Exam were online but really difficult

Lectures have info that is not on slides but we must find in textbook. We are tested on material that he barely covers. He goes on tangents about his life for most of the lecture. It is unclear which information we should take down when he talks. Test questions are unclear and long. Must study for tests. Positive: online tests (open book)
Lectures are very dry and kind of confusing. I like the online forums but I found the test questions unclear.

He will ask you to buy a textbook but you don't really need it. Midterms and exam are all online and he encourages you to use your notes. If you show up to class and take notes or even just use his slides, you will pass! I suggest putting your/his notes into a doc so you can commandF when looking for answers when doing his midterms/exams.

Very gentle man who really cares about his students. Assignments are easy, and exams are challenging but are open book. He does have a light voice and a heavy accent but I got used to it after one lecture and could understand him perfectly.

Hes a very sweet man! The book is a must, all his notes and exams are based off of it. The class itself is kind of dry, but he cares about his students. The tests and assignments are pretty easy and gives great feedback
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I know there's a lot of negative comments, but he is honestly a good prof. He speaks softly and has a heavy accent, but I got used to it about 20 mins into the first lecture and had no issues understanding him for the rest of the semester. He really wants his students to succeed! Super nice guy, very clear expectations. Definitely buy the book!!!!!
Super sweet professor! Really cares about his students and will answer any question you might have! You just need to read the textbook
Not structured at all. This is supposed to be a physiology/biology class and he can only talk about psychology. This is truly frustrating.

Lectures are not structured, his power points are totally empty. He goes off on rants without explaining the relation with the class itself and expect us to know and understand these rants for exams. No explication of concepts or definition. You basically have to read the textbook and teach the class to yourself.

Prof Gottret clearly tries very hard but he speaks so softly that you cannot understand a word he says even when he wears a mic. He also has an extremely think accent which makes him even more impossible to understand. His midterms were ok but he came up with super random questions that weren't taught or in the textbook.

Prof is IMPOSSIBLE to understand. He speaks french with an accent and very very very softly even with the use of a microphone. His voice is very high pitch, so it makes it hard to understand what he is saying. He also walks around in circles during the class. You need to sit super close to him, in order to understand what he is trying to say.

He's from South America so he has a Spanish accent but after a class or 2 you will get used to it and understand him well. He is a nice professor and he does put effort into his course. He shows videos as part of his lectures to ensure the students learn course content and who doesn't like videos? I can tell he has a passion for developmental psych
He is a nice person. I could not understand a single word. I skipped every class, read the book, and got an A.

I didn't mind him, and did not find the course content difficult. Yes, he is hard to understand because he is a very soft speaker, I just sat closer and it was fine. He is very good at responding to emails.
Professeur très gentil, cependant ses examen sont assez difficiles.
With the amount of studying I made, I don't deserve the grade I got. He made me hate psychology. AVOID HIM

His accent is very thick and I found it very hard to understand him. I attended every lecture, and I can honestly say that only about 30 people showed up to his lectures every week when there were about 200 registered for the course. Lectures were not useful, and just studying the slides is enough to achieve a high grade.

Ce cours fut ok mais les examen sont difficiles. Sa formulation des questions est souvent difficile à interpréter.  Ne prenez pas ce professeur-là. Prenez un autre professeur pour des cours de psychologie.

Really kind professor, however.. his exams are not easy and you need to study a lot to do well. I'm in the french section and only one person got an A+ on the first midterm. I always get 90s in psych but his class was much harder.   His final wasn't easy and he doesn't realise that we're not all in Health Sciences. Nice prof, difficult A+. Avoid.

A very genuine individual. Dr. Gottret is smart and he knows so much.  THE CLASS WAS HARD. Midterm and final were both really hard. It's 3 times harder than PSY 1501-02. His final was caotic with a lot of hard questions. Only 1 person got an A+. AVOID   You need to study for a straight 2 weeks to get an A+. Only one person got an A+ (91%).

Very difficult to understand what he is saying because his mic is ALWAYS muffled. Need to sit right in front of him to hear him at all. Slides are directly section by section from textbook and he rarely strays, other than youtube videos. Skipping class is completely doable, as long as you read the textbook and study all the slides. A lot of info!

Lectures were extremely long and very dull. It was almost impossible to understand him. He seems like a very genuine person, however his class was just a regurgitation of the textbook. You  could stay home and read and understand better than you would if you went to class.

Not a terrible prof, but he can be a very dry lecturer so I wouldn't recommend a 3 hour class. His accent is hard to understand sometimes especially because he speaks softly. Course was a midterm, 2 online discussions and a final. Easy grade if you read the textbook.

This course consisted of three exams that were all entirely MC, plus two Forum Discussions. His lectures focus on the textbook, which is what the exams are based on. He will give away a bit of information about what will (and won't) be on the exam. Very reasonable, helpful, and clear expectations. I got 95% in this course. Highly recommended.

Looks like a character from the French Revolution and has very dramatic hand gestures when he talks. Really hard to understand at first because of his accent, but you get used to it and he's very sweet! Easy marker, just read the textbook and you're set. "So interesting!"

An excellent professor overall. The Forum Discussions were very interesting and engaging (fair grading). His exams are also easy as long as you read the textbook. He is extremely helpful in letting students know what to focus on for each exam. His expectations are very clear, but his thick accent can hinder clarity. Overall, I recommend this prof.

Hi's an amazing teacher! If you go to his office you will learn alot about the course and him! He's really helpfull. The exams are weirdo and little bit Hard. So make sure to study very well and learn by hearth what he says to learn. In brief, he is nice!

He is extremely hard to understand and not at all engaging. He literately copy pastes things into his slide from the book and teaches that. He occasionally uses videos to show more info so he puts them on the tests. If it wasn't for the videos, there would be no point going to class at all. Textbook mandatory if you want to pass.
Okay professor, extremely easy midterm, final, and assignments. Can easily learn all of the material from the textbook without attending class.

The nicest person you will ever meet and absolutely hilarious.However, he is quite difficult to understand.The texte book is mandatory not only for the midterms but for the final exams since it's from the book that they form all the questions by.A lot of people never went to class and did great in the class. If you want to laugh, go to class !
Can barely understand what he is saying. Basically taught myself the course, so the textbook is essential. He does have cute quirks, but three hour lectures were brutal.

He truly is a nice and sweet guy. Extremely knowledgeable on the subject . Almost impossible to understand a word he says. He practically speaks in a whisper so I strongly recommend to pay close attention. I missed a few courses and was still able to get high marks thanks to the book. So GET THE BOOK it helps a lot

Sweet, knowledgable prof. Has cute little quirks. Has a very thick accent and a very soft voice. If French is no your first language, do not take his course. You can get by with a fine mark just reading the textbook, but the midterms are half from the text and half from what he teaches in class, so going is recommended.
He's super sweet and his classes are pretty interesting
Awesome

I took 2 classes with him (one in english, one in french) - he's so sweet, but you can't understand a word he says. EXTREMELY knowledgeable. Received an A in both Cross Cultural and Language Dev because I read the textbooks. He is very committed to his students' success. Its an easy grade,  but you have to be willing to put up with the lectures

SUPER nice guy. You can tell that he really cares about his students. He's also very funny. However, he's a really low talker which makes him very difficult to follow, partly because u cant hear and partly because ur falling asleep. His exams are somewhat easy but kind of hard to study for cuz its not clear what will be covered.

Very nice professor.  He's also very enthusiastic about the topic.  His exams are EASY - read the text and you'll be fine.  Also, no tricks on them at all.  I found him a bit difficult to understand partly because he's a very quiet talker. I recommend this class for anyone who needs a 3000 level psych elective.
Can't understand this man!! Seriously, he has a very heavy accent that makes it almost impossible to understand what he's saying.
He keep talking about non relating subject. I got better mark not going in class and just reading the book...
Very nice and helpful teacher! He wants his students to succeed. If you like open book exams take his class for sure!
No Comments
